{"title_page": "Alex Clark (animator)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|American YouTuber, animator, performer}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name = Alex Clark\n| logo =\n| logo caption = Alex in 2017\n| image = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = Massachusetts\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = American\n| occupation = YouTuber, animator, comedian \n| website = {{url|https://itsalexclark.com/}}\n| pseudonym = \n| channel_name = itsAlexClark\n| years_active = 2009\u2013present\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* Animation\n* Comedy\n}}\n| subscribers = 4.37 million\n| subscriber_date = {{start date|2020|3|11}}\n| views = 450 million\n| view_date = {{start date|2020|1|11}}\n| network = [[Studio71]] (previously [[Channel Frederator Network]])\n| associated_acts = [[James Rallison|TheOdd1sOut]],<br>[[Matthew Santoro]],<br>Pam on Sunset\n| catchphrase(s) = 'A Lotta Nada'\n| silver_button = yes\n| silver_year = 2015\n| gold_button = yes\n| gold_year = 2017\n| diamond_button = \n| diamond_year = \n| ruby_button = \n| ruby_year = \n| stats_update = \n}}\n\n'''Alex Clark''' is an American [[YouTube]] animator, juggler, and comedian, based in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].<ref name=ej/> His YouTube channel, '''itsAlexClark''', features humorous animated videos depicting moments from his life, documentaries about his road trips, and many other types of videos.<ref name=tf/><ref name=jg/> As a YouTuber, he is partnered with [[Studio71]],<ref name=tf/> and his channel was nominated for a [[Streamy Award]] for best animated YouTube channel.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/08/streamy-awards-nominations-casey-neistat-lilly-singh-king-bach-brown-girls-dj-khaled-rihanna-kevin-durant-logan-paul-1202153337/ |title=7th Annual Streamy Awards: Casey Neistat, Lilly Singh, \u2018Mr. Student Body President\u2019 Among Nominees |last=Ramos |first=Dino-Ray |date=August 22, 2017 |website=Deadline |lang